The protection of your personal data and your privacy is a central concern for the operator of this website. In the context of using this private website, no personal data is generally collected, stored, or passed on to third parties. The website does not use tracking tools, cookies, or analysis services that could collect personal data.

However, if you transmit personal data (e.g., by contacting us via email), this is done voluntarily and at your own risk. The transmitted data will be used exclusively to process your request and will not be passed on to third parties, unless the operator is legally obliged to do so or you have expressly consented. Please note that data transmission over the internet (e.g., communication via email) may have security vulnerabilities. A complete protection of the data against access by third parties is not possible.

You have the right to request information about the personal data stored about you, its origin and recipient, and the purpose of storage at any time. You can also request the correction, blocking, or deletion of this data, provided that there are no legal retention obligations to the contrary. The operator reserves the right to refuse requests without giving reasons if they are not related to this website.

